  <p>Scotland is a part of the United Kingdom. It is home to around 800 small islands, notable ones being the northern
  isles of Shetland and Orkney, the Hebrides, etc. Scotland is surrounded by a various bodies of waters including the 
  North Sea in the east, the Atlantic Ocean in the north and west, and the Irish Sea in the south-west. Scotland is known for
  the countries beautiful highlands, vivid nature, and fascinating culture with a rich medieval history.
  Itâ€™s not hard to see why the national animal of Scotland is the Unicorn, as it is truly a magical country.

